g.text: The Novus: SustainabilityJulian Wilkinson & Joris Simaitis
A Battery Designed with the Life Cycle in MindLow-Carbon, Abundant and Just Materials Eliminating critical Ni, Co and Mn materials shows a 60% reduction in resource depletion2656
Manufactured in UK’s 2030 Low Carbon GridLeveraging UK’s future battery capacity and rapid renewable deployment for 2030
A Plug-in Hybrid with Optimized EV-ICE modes
70 km battery range meets daily US commuter needs, enabling 92% of the vehicles lifetime to be driven in EV mode
The remaining 8% of driving distance met by the ICE mode such as longer, motorway trips –eliminating range anxiety
The lowest carbon footprint vehicle over from 170,000 km. A correctly, non-excessive battery combined with a super fuel-efficient ICE

Sustainable material assessmentThe diagram to the right shows the dry materials of the 2015 Prius PHV proportioned by weightand supply risk, and colour-coded by the circularityof each material, taken as the average of the recycled input rate for new vehicles, and the effective recovery rate at end-of-life.For example, with current best practices, the Novus could be made using 75% recycled lithium in its traction battery, and 93% could be recovered for re-use at end-of-life, giving an average circularity index of 84, and so lithium is shown in dark green.Hotspots in the 2015 Prius PHV•Much more iron than aluminium; scope for light-weighting•Cobalt in the traction battery and neodymium in motor magnets are significant supply risks•Direct glass re-use is low due to difficulty of separating PVB laminate•Difficult to use recycled silicon in electronics due to the high purity required, but no alternatives available•Bioplastic use can be greatly increased (100% bioplastic concept car was built in 2018!)Improved materials in the 2030 Novus•Maximum use of aluminium for 9% lighter body and 11% lower CO2•No cobalt in traction battery•Ferrite motor magnets reduce use of neodymium and dysprosium by 75%•Doubled use of bioplastics for lower fossil fuel use and lower carbon emissions•North American-grown guayule rubber increases sustainability of tyres.Going even further with the 2030 NovusWith improved manufacturing and recovery processes, and research to expand lab-proven techniques to the industrial scale, the Novus could be produced with:•At least 65% recycled steel and aluminium alloys•At least 50% recycled windscreen glass•At least 50% recycled neodymium and dysprosium, with 60-80% recovery of these metals at end of life (current rate is about 30%), sourcing also from e-waste streams: flat-screen displays, speakers and hard disk drives•Investment in these improvements would benefit the whole of Toyota North America, and the health of all life on the planet.Materials in the 2015 Prius PHVMaterials in the 2030 NovusMaterials in the 2030 Novuswith improved manufacturing and recovery processes
